---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Colophon · uxward">
  <style>
    .top { padding-top: var(--space-8); padding-bottom: var(--space-7); }
    .top a.back {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--tertiary);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .top a.back:hover { color: var(--signature); }

    .title-block { padding-top: var(--space-9); padding-bottom: var(--space-10); }
    .title-eyebrow {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--tertiary);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
    }
    h1.title {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: clamp(48px, 6.4vw, 96px);
      line-height: 1;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      word-spacing: 0;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 30;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin: 0;
    }
    h1.title em {
      font-style: italic; font-weight: 400;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 100, 'WONK' 1;
    }
    .opening {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-style: italic;
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: var(--body);
      max-width: 660px;
      margin: var(--space-7) 0 0;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 36, 'SOFT' 80, 'WONK' 1;
    }

    .section {
      padding: var(--space-10) 0;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    }
    .section-eyebrow {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--tertiary);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    }
    .section-head {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: 36px;
      line-height: 1.1;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin: 0 0 var(--space-9) 0;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 30;
      max-width: 720px;
    }
    .section-head em {
      font-style: italic; font-weight: 400;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 100, 'WONK' 1;
    }

    .spec { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
    .spec-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr 280px;
      gap: var(--space-7);
      padding: var(--space-6) 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
      align-items: baseline;
    }
    .spec-row .key {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--tertiary);
    }
    .spec-row .name {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 26px;
      line-height: 1.2;
      color: var(--ink);
      letter-spacing: -0.012em;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 48, 'SOFT' 30;
    }
    .spec-row .name.mono {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 22px;
      letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    }
    .spec-row .name .why {
      display: block;
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 16.5px;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: var(--body);
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 24, 'SOFT' 80, 'WONK' 1;
      margin-top: var(--space-3);
      max-width: 520px;
    }
    .spec-row a.src {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 16px;
      color: var(--ink);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 4px;
      text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
      text-align: right;
      min-width: 0;
      overflow-wrap: anywhere;
    }
    .spec-row a.src:hover { color: var(--signature); }

    .color-list { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
    .color-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 80px 200px 1fr 120px;
      gap: var(--space-7);
      padding: var(--space-5) 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
      align-items: center;
    }
    .swatch {
      width: 56px;
      height: 56px;
      border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    }
    .color-row .token-name {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 1.2;
      color: var(--ink);
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 48, 'SOFT' 30;
    }
    .color-row .role {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 16.5px;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: var(--body);
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 24, 'SOFT' 80, 'WONK' 1;
      max-width: 480px;
    }
    .color-row .hex {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 13px;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      color: var(--tertiary);
      text-align: right;
    }

    .build-list { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
    .build-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr 280px;
      gap: var(--space-7);
      padding: var(--space-5) 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
      align-items: baseline;
    }
    .build-row .key {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--tertiary);
    }
    .build-row .what {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 19px;
      line-height: 1.45;
      color: var(--ink);
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 24, 'SOFT' 30;
    }
    .build-row .what em {
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--body);
      font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 24, 'SOFT' 80, 'WONK' 1;
    }
    .build-row a.src {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 16px;
      color: var(--ink);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 4px;
      text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
      text-align: right;
      min-width: 0;
      overflow-wrap: anywhere;
    }
    .build-row a.src:hover { color: var(--signature); }

    .ack-prose p {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 19px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--body);
      max-width: 660px;
      margin: 0 0 var(--space-6);
    }
    .ack-prose p strong { font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink); }
    .ack-prose p em { font-style: italic; }

    .stamp-row {
      padding: var(--space-9) 0 var(--space-10);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: baseline;
      gap: var(--space-7);
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .stamp-row .stamp {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--tertiary);
    }
    .stamp-row .fleuron {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 22px;
      color: var(--tertiary);
      letter-spacing: 0;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .spec-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .spec-row a.src { text-align: left; }
      .color-row { grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr; }
      .color-row .role { display: none; }
      .build-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .build-row a.src { text-align: left; }
    }
  </style>

  <div class="container top">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="marker">§ ↩</div>
      <div><a class="back" href="/">— Back home</a></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container title-block">
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="marker">§ 00</div>
      <div>
        <div class="title-eyebrow">— Colophon · How this was made —</div>
        <h1 class="title">A note on the <em>making.</em></h1>
        <p class="opening">
          uxward.com is a working journal of Brandon E. B. Ward — designed in light and dark,
          built with restraint, set in two faces, and revised quarterly. Most visitors will
          never see this page. If you're reading it, hello. You're the right kind of reader.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="marker">§ 01</div>
        <div>
          <div class="section-eyebrow">— Typography —</div>
          <h2 class="section-head">Two faces, <em>one in service of the other.</em></h2>
          <div class="spec">
            <div class="spec-row">
              <span class="key">— Display &amp; body —</span>
              <span class="name">
                Fraunces
                <span class="why">A variable serif by Undercase Type. Chosen for its WONK and SOFT axes — a face that can be sober at body size and slightly mischievous in italics, without ever being decorative.</span>
              </span>
              <a class="src" href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Fraunces" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Undercase Type →</a>
            </div>
            <div class="spec-row">
              <span class="key">— Eyebrows &amp; metadata —</span>
              <span class="name mono">
                JetBrains Mono
                <span class="why">A monospace from JetBrains. Used only for small labels, eyebrows, and stamps — the parts of the page that read as administrative rather than editorial.</span>
              </span>
              <a class="src" href="https://www.jetbrains.com/lp/mono/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">JetBrains →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="marker">§ 02</div>
        <div>
          <div class="section-eyebrow">— Color —</div>
          <h2 class="section-head">Five tokens. <em>One of them is rationed.</em></h2>
          <div class="color-list">
            <div class="color-row">
              <div class="swatch" style="background: #FFFFFF;"></div>
              <div class="token-name">Canvas</div>
              <div class="role">The page. The bias toward white over off-white is the bias toward editorial seriousness.</div>
              <div class="hex">#FFFFFF</div>
            </div>
            <div class="color-row">
              <div class="swatch" style="background: #FAF8F4;"></div>
              <div class="token-name">Paper</div>
              <div class="role">The tinted off-white. Used for callout bands and the case-study artifact frames.</div>
              <div class="hex">#FAF8F4</div>
            </div>
            <div class="color-row">
              <div class="swatch" style="background: #040404;"></div>
              <div class="token-name">Ink</div>
              <div class="role">The headlines, the wordmark, the body. Not pure black; black with the warmth dialed down by one degree.</div>
              <div class="hex">#040404</div>
            </div>
            <div class="color-row">
              <div class="swatch" style="background: #6B6B6B;"></div>
              <div class="token-name">Tertiary</div>
              <div class="role">The mono labels, the timestamps, the rules. Quiet by design.</div>
              <div class="hex">#6B6B6B</div>
            </div>
            <div class="color-row">
              <div class="swatch" style="background: #CC0006;"></div>
              <div class="token-name">Signature red</div>
              <div class="role">Rationed across the site. Five sanctioned places. Never a button color, never a hover state, never a divider. Always a moment.</div>
              <div class="hex">#CC0006</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="marker">§ 03</div>
        <div>
          <div class="section-eyebrow">— Build —</div>
          <h2 class="section-head">The stack, <em>told briefly.</em></h2>
          <div class="build-list">
            <div class="build-row">
              <span class="key">— Framework —</span>
              <span class="what">Astro — <em>static-first, content-shaped, the right tool for a journal.</em></span>
              <a class="src" href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">astro.build →</a>
            </div>
            <div class="build-row">
              <span class="key">— Hosting —</span>
              <span class="what">Cloudflare Pages — <em>fast, cheap, paid for in five-year increments.</em></span>
              <a class="src" href="https://pages.cloudflare.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">pages.cloudflare.com →</a>
            </div>
            <div class="build-row">
              <span class="key">— Content —</span>
              <span class="what">Markdown — <em>essays and case studies authored in the format I'll still be able to read in 2046.</em></span>
              <a class="src" href="https://commonmark.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">commonmark.org →</a>
            </div>
            <div class="build-row">
              <span class="key">— Domain —</span>
              <span class="what">uxward.com — <em>registered 2014, used in earnest 2026.</em></span>
              <span class="src">— —</span>
            </div>
            <div class="build-row">
              <span class="key">— Source —</span>
              <span class="what">Public on GitHub. <em>The site itself is part of the work.</em></span>
              <a class="src" href="https://github.com/brandonebward/uxward" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/brandonebward/uxward →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="marker">§ 04</div>
        <div>
          <div class="section-eyebrow">— Acknowledgments —</div>
          <h2 class="section-head">Borrowed, <em>with thanks.</em></h2>
          <div class="ack-prose">
            <p>
              The editorial discipline of this site is borrowed from <strong>Khoi Vinh's</strong>
              twenty years of restraint at Subtraction.com, and from the <strong>New Yorker's</strong>
              insistence that a serious face does not need to be a quiet one. The decision to
              keep red rationed across exactly five places came from looking, for a long time,
              at how Penguin paperback covers earned their one accent in the 1960s.
            </p>
            <p>
              The case for the working journal — over the portfolio, over the case-study deck,
              over the LinkedIn — comes from <strong>Frank Chimero</strong>, <strong>Robin
              Sloan</strong>, and the body of long-form writing that quietly insists the personal
              site is still the right primitive. <em>It is.</em>
            </p>
            <p>
              The <strong>Fraunces</strong> family was developed by Undercase Type and Phaedra
              Charles. The <strong>JetBrains Mono</strong> family was developed by JetBrains.
              Both are open-source, and both are responsible for whatever this site reads as.
            </p>
            <p>
              And to the reader who got to the bottom of the colophon: <em>thank you for
              looking.</em> You are why the site is here.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="stamp-row">
      <span class="stamp">— Last revised Q2 2026 · Updated quarterly · Brandon E. B. Ward · Dallas —</span>
      <span class="fleuron" aria-hidden="true">❦</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
